<u>NAME</u>
<b>Arduino Happy Birthday Emitter</b>

<u>DESCRIPTION</u>
<b>Using an 8 ohm speaker rescued from a defunct <a href="http://www.irobot.com/">iRobot Scooba</a>, some radio wire from an underground dog fence, an <a href="http://www.arduino.cc/en/Main/ArduinoBoardDuemilanove">Arduino Duemilanove</a> procured from <a href="http://adafruit.com/">http://adafruit.com/</a>, and a tone demo sketch from <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/en/Tutorial/BuiltInExamples/toneMelody">https://www.arduino.cc/en/Tutorial/BuiltInExamples/toneMelody</a> , the kids and I made a Happy Birthday emitter for mom.  Happy Birthday Amy!
</b>

<b>
<p>Here are the <a href="https://gist.github.com/2820669">happybirthdayemitter.pde</a> sketch and accompanying <a href="https://gist.github.com/2820675">pitches.h</a> header file.
</p>
</b>
